  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We characterize the Schatten class Toeplitz operators induced by a positive Borel measure on the unit disc and the reproducing kernel of the Bergman space <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></math> , where ω is a radial weight satisfying the doubling property <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mo>∫</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><mi>ω</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"></mspace><mi>d</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi>C</mi><msubsup><mrow><mo>∫</mo></mrow><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msubsup><mi>ω</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>s</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"></mspace><mi>d</mi><mi>s</mi></math> . By using this, we describe the Schatten class composition operators. We also discuss basic properties of composition operators acting from <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msubsup></math> to <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msubsup><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></msubsup></math> .</subfield>
